This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with temporal activity detection in videos using a convolutional neural network. It may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with processing and analyzing video data. The use of deep learning techniques suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves classification of activity categories, which suggests it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it involves detecting and retrieving specific information from videos.
